Minister Zweli Mkhize confirms total of 709 cases of Coronavirus COVID-19 25 March 2020 As of today, the confirmed cases of COVID-19 in South Africa have risen by 155. This brings the total number of confirmed cases to 709 Gauteng 319 Western Cape 183 KwaZulu Natal 91 Free State 30 North West 5 Mpumalanga 8 Limpopo 4 Eastern Cape 2 Northern Cape 2 Unallocated 65 Issued by Department of Health, 24 March 2020  